Thailand Seeks 430 Billion Baht for Utility Debt, Krungthep Says

-- B y   A n u c h i t   N g u y e n
-- 
2011-09-20T01:27:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-20/thailand-seeks-430-billion-baht-for-utility-debt-krungthep-says.html
Thailand ’s finance ministry seeks
to raise about 430 billion baht ($14 billion) to repay debt at
state-owned utilities, Krungthep Turakij reported, citing
Areepong Bhoocha-oom, the ministry’s permanent secretary.  Most of the debt is with State Railways of Thailand,
Bangkok Mass Transity Authority and Bank for Agriculture and
Agricultural Cooperatives, which have been used by the
government to implement its economic policies, the Thai-language
newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anuchit Nguyen in Bangkok at 
 anguyen@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Daniel Ten Kate at 
 dtenkate@bloomberg.net  